videos.description: Will Grier finds David Sills V for a 34-yard completion down the sideline.
videos.headline: West Virginia's Sills shifts momentum with big catch

videos.description: Sam Ehlinger takes a shot down field and Reggie Hemphill-Mapps is there to catch it to pick up 50 yards.
videos.headline: Texas' Ehlinger connects with Hemphill-Mapps for huge play

videos.description: Sam Ehlinger finds Kendall Moore on a quick pass play and he takes it in for a 4-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Longhorns' Moore scores first TD of the game

videos.description: West Virginia QB Will Grier is rushed to the locker room after injuring his throwing hand against Texas.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Grier injured diving for pylon) 2017/11/18 ESHEET

videos.headline: Grier injured diving for pylon

videos.description: Sam Ehlinger hands the ball to former QB Jerrod Heard and he  throws it back to Ehlinger who picks up 23 yards.
videos.headline: Texas' Ehlinger showing versatility on trick play

videos.description: Sam Ehlinger  has a couple of defenders running unblocked in his direction, but he eludes both of them to pick up 17 yards and a first down.
videos.headline: Longhorns' Ehlinger uses quick feet to convert critical 3rd down

videos.description: Sam Ehlinger fakes the play-action pass and finds Chris Warren lll down the middle for a 20-yard touchdown to go up 14-0.
videos.headline: Texas extends lead with Warren TD

videos.description: Sam Ehlinger takes the QB keeper and jukes the defender for a 16-yard gain.
videos.headline: Longhorns' Ehlinger showing video game moves

videos.description: Tom Herman says he planned for Sam Ehlinger to be the starter after the 3rd series based on his play in the game.
videos.headline: Herman: 'Ehlinger was playing well'

videos.description: Sam Ehlinger throws the ball while under pressure and is intercepted by CB Kenny Robinson, who returns it for a 94-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: West Virginia gets back in it with pick-six

videos.description: Kyle Porter finds a gap and runs it for a 10-yard touchdown to put Texas up 21-7.
videos.headline: Porter's TD gives Texas double-digit lead

videos.description: Chris Chugunov finds Ka'Raun White for a 12-yard touchdown to close the gap 21-14.
videos.headline: West Virginia TD on 4th down cuts the lead

videos.description: Chris Chugunov is sacked by Gary Johnson and he fumbles the ball, CB Chris Nelson recovers.
videos.headline: West Virginia commits costly turnover

videos.description: Daniel Young leaps over the defense to score a 1-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Young's TD widens Texas' lead

videos.description: Longhorns players celebrate on the sideline as Texas becomes bowl eligible with their 28-14 win over West Virginia.
videos.headline: Texas sideline dances to victory
